e the selective factors of exposed sites have a weaker effect. Thus, changes in the mutational bias produce deep effects on the biophysical properties of the protein (hydrophobicity) and on its evolutionary properties (sequence entropy and substitution rate) at the same time. The program Prot-evol that implements the two site-specific substitution processes is freely available at https://ub.cbm.uam.es/prot-fold-evol/prot-fold-evol-soft-main.php\#Prot-Evol.},
